ebox/Header|type=Fire|type2=Fighting}}\n{{Spritebox/NA|gen=IV}}\n{{Spritebox/4|ndex=391}}\n{{Spritebox/5|ndex=391}}\n{{Spritebox/6|ndex=391}}\n{{Spritebox/7|ndex=391}}\n{{Spritebox/Footer|391|Monferno}}\n\n==Trivia==\n* Monferno shares its {{pkmn|category}} with {{p|Pancham}}. They are both known as the Playful Pokémon.\n\n===Origin===\nMonferno may be based on a {{wp|golden snub-nosed monkey}} or a {{wp|mandrill}}, a primate similar to a {{wp|baboon}}. It also appears to be a direct impression of the {{wp|Monkey Kung Fu}}, a type of martial arts, which could explain its {{t|Fighting}} type.\n\n====Name origin====\nMonferno is a combination of \'\'{{wp|monkey}}\'\' and \'\'inferno\'\'.\n\nMoukazaru is a combination of 猛火 \'\'mōka\'\' (roaring flames) and 猿 \'\'saru\'\' (monkey).\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Fire|type2=Fighting\n|ja=モウカザル \'\'Moukazaru\'\'|jameaning=From {{tt|猛火 \'\'mōka\'\'|roaring flames}} and {{tt|猿 \'\'saru\'\'|monkey}}\n|fr=Chimpenfeu|frmeaning=From \'\'{{tt|chimpanzé|chimapanze}}\'\' and \'\'{{tt|en feu|on fire}}\'\'\n|es=Monferno|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Panpyro|demeaning=From \'\'{{tt|Schimpanse|chimpanzee}}\'\' and \'\'pyro\'\'\n|it=Monferno|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=파이숭이 \'\'Paisoongi\'\'|komeaning=From \'\'fire\'\' and {{tt|원숭이 \'\'wonsung\'i\'\'|monkey}}\n|zh_cmn=猛火猴 \'\'Měnghuǒhóu\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=Literally "Fierce fire monkey"\n<!--|zh_yue=猛火猴 \'\'Máahngfóhàuh\'\'|zh_yuemeaning=Same as Mandarin name-->\n}}\n<br clear="left">\n\n==Related articles==\n* [[Ash\'s Monferno]]\n* [[Flint\'s Monferno]]\n* [[Chimler]]\n* [[Mitsumi\'s Monferno]]\n* [[Yū Shirogane\'s Monferno]]\n* [[Starter Pokémon]]\n\n==External links==\n\n{{-}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Fire|type2=Fighting}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Fire|prevnum=390|prev=Chimchar|nextnum=392|next=Infernape}}\n|}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[de:Panpyro]]\n[[es:Monferno]]\n[[fr:Chimpenfeu]]\n[[it:Monferno]]\n[[ja:モウカザル]]\n[[zh:猛火猴]]'}